de.lambeck.pned.filesystem

Class FSInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.lambeck.pned.filesystem.FSInfo

  • public class FSInfo
extends java.lang.Object
    Class for conversion of path names (e.g. into canonical path names) and checks if files exist.

    Note: canonical path names are unique and thus we can use them as identifiers for the open files and models. (See: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/io/File.html#getCanonicalPath--)
    Author:
    Thomas Lambeck, 4128320

      • getSaveAsFullName

        public static java.lang.String getSaveAsFullName(javax.swing.JFrame parentComponent,
                                                 ApplicationController controller,
                                                 I18NManager i18n)
        Adds additional parameters for references to ApplicationController and I18NManager to getSaveAsFullName(JFrame parentComponent).

        Uses the reference to the ApplicationController to get the last path used by the user.
        Uses the reference to the I18NManager for localized messages in case of errors.
        Parameters:
        parentComponent - The parent component (should be the main application window)
        controller - The application controller
        i18n - The manager for localized strings
        Returns:
        Null if the user cancelled the operation; otherwise the canonical (unique) path name
